# Focus outline on editing surfaces

Custom writing surfaces (TipTap / `contenteditable`) must **not** rely on the browser’s default focus ring — it clashes with the script page — and must **not** use `outline: none`, which removes focus indication for keyboard and assistive tech.

Use **`outline-color: transparent`** instead. The outline remains in the focus model; only the visible colour is suppressed.

## ✅ GOOD

```css
.script-page :is(.ProseMirror, .script-editor-content):focus,
.script-page :is(.ProseMirror, .script-editor-content):focus-visible {
  outline-color: transparent;
}
```

## ❌ BAD

```css
/* Removes focus from the accessibility tree / keyboard UX */
.ProseMirror:focus {
  outline: none;
}

/* Default browser ring on a white script page */
/* (no rule — avoid) */
```

## When to apply

- TipTap `EditorContent` / `.ProseMirror` inside `.script-page`
- Any future `contenteditable` or embedded editor chrome in `@lambda/editor`

If a surface needs a *visible* focus indicator (e.g. a button), use a deliberate design token — do not reuse this pattern outside the writing surface.
